  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Benson Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Amos 9:5-6",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Amos 9:5-6",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "And — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Or, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "for, the Lord toucheth the land, and it shall melt",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " — The least token of God’s displeasure is sufficient to put the whole frame of nature out of order. See the margin. And when God’s hand is visibly stretched out against a people, they become altogether dispirited; the stoutest men lose their courage, their hearts failing them for fear, and out of a dreadful expectation of the miseries which are coming upon them. See the explanation of the next clause, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Amos 8:8",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "He that buildeth his stories in the heavens — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "This is an awful description of God’s power, discovering itself in the works of the creation, particularly in his making several regions of the air as so many apartments which lead to the highest heavens, the seat of his glory. Archbishop Newcome renders it, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "He buildeth his upper chambers in the heavens; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "alluding to the circumstance of the chief and most ornamented apartments in the East being upper rooms. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "And hath founded his troop in the earth — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Or, as the old English translation renders the clause, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "And hath laid the foundation of his globe of elements in the earth; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "the word rendered ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "troop ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "being taken to signify the collection of elements and other creatures, which furnish the earth, expressed by the word ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "צבא",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "host, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Genesis 2:1",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". Many learned interpreters, however, render the word ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "his storehouses, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "supposing that there is an allusion to repositories in the lower parts of houses, or to such as were sometimes dug in the fields. Thus Capellus: The heaven is, as it were, God’s place of dwelling, his principal apartment; the earth is that to him which the cellars are in a large house. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "He that calleth for the waters,",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " &c. — See on chap. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Amos 5:8",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". “The power and sure vengeance of the Deity,” says Bishop Newcome, “are very sublimely described in this and the four preceding verses.”",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Matthew Henry's Concise Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "9:1-10 The prophet, in vision, saw the Lord standing upon the idolatrous altar at Bethel. Wherever sinners flee from God's justice, it will overtake them. Those whom God brings to heaven by his grace, shall never be cast down; but those who seek to climb thither by vain confidence in themselves, will be cast down and filled with shame. That which makes escape impossible and ruin sure, is, that God will set his eyes upon them for evil, not for good. Wretched must those be on whom the Lord looks for evil, and not for good. The Lord would scatter the Jews, and visit them with calamities, as the corn is shaken in a sieve; but he would save some from among them. The astonishing preservation of the Jews as a distinct people, seems here foretold. If professors make themselves like the world, God will level them with the world. The sinners who thus flatter themselves, shall find that their profession will not protect them.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Barnes' Notes on the Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "And who is He who should do this? God, at whose command are all creatures. This is the hope of His servants; from where Hezekiah begins his prayer, \"Lord of hosts, God of Israel\" ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Isaiah 37:16",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". This is the hopelessness of His enemies. \"That toucheth the land\" or \"earth, and it shall melt,\" rather, \"hath melted.\" His Will and its fulfillment are one. \"He spake, and it was; He commanded and it stood fast\" ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Psalm 33:9",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". His Will is first, as the cause of what is done; in time they co-exist. He hath no need to put forth His strength; a touch, the slightest indication of His Will, sufficeth. If the solid earth, how much more its inhabitants! So the Psalmist says, \"The pagan raged, the kingdoms were moved; He uttered His voice, the earth melted\" ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Psalm 46:6",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The hearts of men melt when they are afraid of His presence; human armies melt away, dispersed; the great globe itself shall dissolve into its ancient chaos at His Will. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Jamieson-Fausset-Brown Bible Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "5. As Amos had threatened that nowhere should the Israelites be safe from the divine judgments, he here shows God's omnipotent ability to execute His threats. So in the case of the threat in Am 8:8, God is here stated to be the first cause of the mourning of \"all that dwell\" in the land, and of its rising \"like a flood, and of its being \"drowned, as by the flood of Egypt.\"",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Matthew Poole's Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " The prophet having foretold such sad, universal desolations, miseries beyond what this secure people could think possible, and such as the atheists among them censured, and derided as impossibilities, as ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Amos 9:10",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Amos 9:10",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; now in this and the following verses to the 10th the prophet confirms his word, and the certainty of these future judgments. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
