  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Pulpit Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_sub_title",
        "text": "Verse 5.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - To confirm the threats just uttered, the prophet dwells upon God's omnipotence, of which he gives instances. He who will do this is ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "the Lord God of hosts",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", There is no copula in the Hebrew here. (So ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Amos 4:13",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Amos 5:8",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".) This title, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "Jehovah Elohim Zebaoth",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", represents God not only as Ruler of the heavenly bodies, but as the Monarch of a multitude of heavenly spirits who execute his will, worship him in his abiding place, and are attendants and witnesses of his glory (see note on Haggai 1:2). ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "Shall melt;",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "σαλεύων",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " (Septuagint); comp. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Psalm 46:6",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Psalm 97:5",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Micah 1:4",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Nahum 1:5",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The expression denotes the destructive effects of the judgments of God. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "Shall mourn.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " The last clauses of the verse are a repetition of ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Amos 8:8",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", with some slight variation. Amos 9:5",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
